main event: A sighting of 5 unidentified objects moving in a circular, flamed pattern in San Diego, California on September 30, 1963.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 5 minutes and was observed at 2145Z., The objects moved in a SSW direction., The sightings coincided with the passage of the Echo I satellite., Official reports were created by multiple USAF personnel concerning the incident., The objects were reported to have unusual characteristics, not resembling conventional aircraft.
witness description: Details from various reports, including observations from untrained individuals and military personnel.
